<TITLE> Ports remain on Signal 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)The Met office advised all local ports to maintain their signal-three alert on Sunday, as a low began developing over the northwest Bay and adjoining areas. A Met office bulletin said the low looks likely to intensify and squally weather may affect the north Bay and maritime ports. Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla ports have been advised to keep hoisted local cautionary signal three, the bulletin said. The met office has been advising ports to keep signal three hoisted since Friday. All fishing boats and trawlers in the north Bay have been advised to stay close to the coast and proceed with caution until further notice
